properties.abstract: A perfect 18 km hike along the Grbetaler Hhenweg Path close to the city of Berne, leading along the Lngenberg and Grbetal valley. An ideal hike for those who enjoy views of the distant Alps and have a cultural interest in farmhouses.
properties.description:
Starting point for this hike is Kehrsatz. Following a short climb on the flanks of the Lngenberg, the Grbetaler Hhenweg Path gently leads up and down on a natural trail through fertile land and woods. Dreamlike, untouched landscapes meet the eye of hikers, with stunning snow-capped mountains in the distance and beautiful old farmhouses, further embellished with floral decoration.

Attractions underway are the Falebach Weiler  best-kept hamlet on the Lngenberg  or the might walls of sandstone above Gutenbrnnen, in which rare birds nest. Picnic spots, seating banks and numerous guesthouses cordially invite one to stop, enjoy and take in the scenery.

Across lush meadows, through rows of trees and later downhill along the Mlibach stream, the hike ends in Mhlethurnen with its characteristic Bernese-style farmhouses. Next stop: civilisation.
